xxl.core.io.fat
Class ClusterChainIterator

java.lang.Object
  xxl.core.io.fat.ClusterChainIterator
All Implemented Interfaces:
Iterator
Direct Known Subclasses:
ListClusterChainEntriesIterator
public class ClusterChainIterator
extends Object
implements Iterator

This class iterates over a list of clusters. The object returned by the next method is a byte array representation of the actual cluster.

Constructor Detail

ClusterChainIterator

public ClusterChainIterator(FATDevice device,
                            long clusterNumber,
                            boolean isRoot)
Creates an instance of this object. If the given clusterNumber belongs to the root directory in case of FAT12 or FAT16 the isRoot flag has to be true and the clusterNumber has to be direct. Otherwise the given clusterNumber has to be indirect.

Parameters:
device - object of FATDevice.
clusterNumber - number of cluster where the iteration should start.
isRoot - indicates if the clusterNumber belongs to the root directory.
